# FedRAMP Explorer

This website provides a simple way to browse and search the FedRAMP controls.

## Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [Hugo](https://gohugo.io/)

## Getting Started

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/ScaleSec/fedramp_explorer.git
   cd fedramp_explorer
   ```

2. **Install dependencies:**
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. **Generate data and content:**
   This command processes the raw FedRAMP data, generates the JSON files used by the site, and creates the markdown content files for each control.
   ```bash
   node scripts/process_data.js
   ```

4. **Run the development server:**
   ```bash
   hugo server
   ```
   The site will be available at `http://localhost:1313`.

## Building the Site

To build the static site for deployment, run:
```bash
hugo
```
The generated site will be in the `public` directory.